parameters:
...Seriously, being exiled to a distant island is
tough...ugh...

To be banished to such a remote place just for burglary...
I've got no choice but to sleep in frustration... zzz...
zzz...

(Could it be the Burglary Brothers? Banished all the way out
here as punishment...)

Huh? Who are you? I don't recognize your face. Are you a new
convict?
Yes. My name is Karin. You're Kisanosuke-san, right?

Oh! So you're Karin, huh? I've heard about you. You've
already given those convict leaders a thrashing, haven't
you? As expected of someone who's been exiled, a real
troublemaker. You've got spirit!
Ahaha... Thank you... Kisanosuke-san, are you also an exile?

I was a fisherman in Uraga, but I got hooked on gambling. I
fought too much with cheaters in Edo, got caught by the
officials over and over, and finally got dumped in this
godforsaken place. It's too late for regrets now.
...Um, I have a favor to ask of you, Kisanosuke-san.

Ah. If it's a favor you're asking for, is it a fishing rod?
Sure thing.

...But there's a condition. Hand over all the money you've
got.

That's right. A fishing rod is essential for surviving on
this island. If you don't want to starve to death, leave all
your wealth behind. I'm not running a charity here making
fishing gear, you know. Heh heh heh...
Kisanosuke-san, please don't be so mean to Karin-san.

I'm also asking you. Please give the fishing gear to Karin-
san. She protected me from the convict leaders. She's a very
kind person...

Okay, okay! If it's a request from you, Kachou-san, I can't
refuse! I'll make a brand-new fishing rod right away, so
just wait a moment!

...(This Kisanosuke person, he likes Kachou-san, doesn't
he...)

Here you go, didn't mean to keep you waiting, Karin-san.
Brand new fishing gear. It's sturdy enough to catch even
sharks. Take good care of it.
Wow! Thank you so much, Kisanosuke-san!

You're in luck, Karin-san. Just don't forget the bait for
fishing. If you don't have any, they sell it at the tool
shop.

Thank you as well, Kachou-san! I'll do my best fishing on
the southern beach!

You can sell the fish you catch at the tool shop. If you've
caught too many, selling them is a good way to make some
money. And if you happen to catch a 【Tuna】, bring it to me.
I'll treat you to something delicious♪

Oh!? That's a huge fish, a tuna, isn't it? You did a great
job catching it!
Yes! I caught it by line fishing at the southern beach!

How about it, Karin-san. Could you spare one? I used to be a
chef in Edo, so I can skillfully fillet this tuna.

Wow, really? I'm so happy! I'm terrible at cooking, so
please, I'm counting on you!

Oh my... You caught such a big fish? That's amazing, Karin-
san.

Kachou-san, you're just in time. Kisanosuke-san is about to
cook it for us.
It's a big fish after all. Let's all eat together!

Incredible...! It's so fluffy... It feels like my tongue is
melting...!

Delicious...! This is the first time I've ever eaten such a
delicious fish!

In Edo, because it's fatty, it's unpopular and not eaten
much, called 'cat's stepover' since even cats won't eat it.
But the fatty part like tuna belly is delicious, you know.
It's my favorite.

Yeah, yeah! I had no idea toro was such a delicacy...! It
really is delicious♪ It goes so well with dark soy sauce!

Ufufu. If I hadn't been exiled to this island, I would have
never known.

By the way, Karin-san, have you met the old man with white
hair?

The white-haired...? No, I haven't since I arrived on this
island...

He's an elderly man living in a hut north of my house. He
was sent to Mujou Island on the ship before the one that
brought you here. I've given him some medicine and... once
we got to talking, I found out he's quite knowledgeable
about many things.

Ah, the white-haired monk, right. He does divinations and
predicts the weather and stuff... kind of mysterious, you
know... definitely not an ordinary person...

Hmm, sounds like an interesting person. I'll meet him next
time.

I'm full now. This is in return for the tuna. I'll give you
some fishing bait. Catch a lot more and bring them back,
Karin-san.
Thank you very much, Kisanosuke-san. The meal was wonderful♪

If I could return to Edo, I'd like to open a shop
specializing in fatty tuna. I want to show the folks in Edo
how delicious the fat of tuna can be. Well, it's just a
dream though. Hahaha!
